{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6da849c-c5f2-4e7e-8fb8-b5e077f098f9","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GmGi3k6Bs7Af4qI90Q9onZ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bfa6e1cbbcb54c2ea342c38971a8d7f3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bfa6e1cbbcb54c2ea342c38971a8d7f3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"dd2777fc-83e6-4ca3-809e-bb134b007251","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order.\n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs`\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"5C12:31EDC7:1D05AA5:20D68F1:6A07C84F"},"id":"c468bb5f-4083-4700-acfa-634fa5dc0270","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:54.580Z","parentId":"5384aacb-9dfb-4bf6-a08d-25ba1d587f94"}
